s Congress (APC). Speaking at Itori, Abiodun urged the people of the State to go all out and obtain their Permanent Voters’ Cards (PVCs) adding that they should participate in the forthcoming elections. The governor who described his administration as a promise-keeping government called on residents of the state to vote for all candidates of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the election. “Our administration is a promise-keeping government. We have kept faith in the people and we assure you that as we continue, we will not let you down. “We have commissioned ultra modern lockup shops, and we have commissioned Itori township road. We shall continue to deliver the dividends of democracy to our people. “I have promised to always work for the people and I shall keep my promise. “Oke Mosan (governor’s office) is not a beer parlour, we are not going to squander your resources on projects that will not add value to the people. We are not going to waste your resources on irrelevant things.”  By Nnamdi Ojiego Landlords and residents of Itori Mogan village extension in the neighborhood of Golf Resort in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital, have raised alarm over an alleged demolition exercise carried out by the officials of state government. According to Baale of the community, Olawale Oladipupo, the lingering crisis… In "News" Ogun students inaugurate Campaign Committee for Abiodun’s re-election In "News" By James Ogunnaike Ogun State government on Monday disclosed that in year 2021 Budget, great emphasis would be placed on the relative value and cost of each expenditure item and sub-head. The government said, it would continue to commit resources to complete and fund key infrastructural facilities capable of unlocking… In "News"